                            community returned to their convents in Amida.  <a href="/827-15" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> In 
                                529
                                840
                            , John ordained seventy men from the convents of Amida.  <a href="/816-16" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> The Convent treated all men kindly, zealously feeding,
                            washing, and providing for the poor.  <a href="/809-4" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> When the old
                                man came to the convent, the leaders wanted to give him a place of
                            honor. Instead, he chose to sit at the lowest table, refusing even to
                            bless the food.  <a href="/809-5" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">The old
                            man continuously asked the archimandrite of the Amida convent for
                            a dismissal. Curious, John asks the man about his eating, sleeping, and prayer
                            habits. He eats
                            and prays the way he does out of recognition of human sinfulness.
                         <a href="/809-9" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="sources"><h4>Residence: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">James</span> resided in <span class="tei-placeName">Convent of the
                                    Eddessens</span> near <span class="tei-placeName"> Amida</span>.  <a href="/807-2" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">
                                <span class="tei-persName">Anonymous 3760</span> resided in 
                                <span class="tei-placeName">Convent of the Eddessens</span> near 
                                <span class="tei-placeName"> Amida</span>.  <a href="/807-21" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">John</span> resided in <span class="tei-placeName">the
                                convent</span> adjoining the city of <span class="tei-placeName">Amida</span>.  <a href="/809-3" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Symeon
                                    the Solitary</span> resided in <span class="tei-placeName">a convent adjoining the city
